llected through questionnaires and hemoglobin tests t h e dataset represents 7 million age 8 12 children in poor western counties the anemia prevalence was 34 using the who's hemoglobin cutoff of 120g l students who boarded at school and girls were more likely to be anemic assuming the sample population is representative of poor regions in western china nearly 2.5 million 8 12 year old school children in the region may be anemic and many more iron deficient given china's growth such high prevalence of anemia is surprising and illustrative of the large health disparities in the country iron deficiency remains a significant nutrition issue though there appears to be no effort to address this issue download pdf+ complete modified january 2011 pdf 214_ _alarmingly_high_anemia_p pdf 313.9 kb topics health and medicine china east asia & the pacific stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
